						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Agastyēśvara shrine at the foot of the hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟavarman Kulaśēkharadēva I: Year 22, Āṉi = 1289-90 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete record describes the king as <hi rend="italic">Emmaṇḍalamum-koṇḍaruḷiya.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to the <hi rend="italic">dēvakanmi,</hi> etc., of the temple of Uḍaiyār Tēnāṟṟu-Nāyakar of Tirukkuṉṟakkuḍi, one of the villages, irrigated by (the river) Tēnāṟu in Adalaiyūṟ-nāḍu in Kēraḷasiṅga-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
